channel.title: Mspaint contest?
channel.description: well, fastbawlz recently had that LPOTHM thing, and although the entries were both pretty good, the contest itself sorta failed. so, i was thinking that maybe it would be a better idea to do something less time-consuming, so more people will enter. everyone has paint, and there would be more than one way to go about trying to win. you could go for comedy appeal, or something abstract, or spend a lot of time and make something realistic-looking, which is hard to do in paint. i'll wait to see if this idea picks up any more steam before deciding on dates and more specific rules, but i can think of one problem already: verifying that it was made in paint. can anyone think of a good way to do this? feedback is appreciated.
